    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-10-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1960-10-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="344"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                <head>344. Memorandum of a Conversation, Ciudad Acuña, Mexico, October 24, 1960<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d344fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 711.11–EI/10–2460. Confidential. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_OME1">Osborne</persName> and approved by the White House on
                        November 3.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Mexico</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1960-10-24">October 24,
                            1960</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Meeting of the President with the President of Mexico at Ciudad Acuña,
                        October 24, 1960</item>
                </list>
                <pb facs="0943" n="903" xml:id="pg_903"/>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States</hi>
                        <list>
                            <item>The President</item>
                            <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                            <item>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_HRC1">Hill</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HJC1">Hagerty</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Assistance Secretary <persName corresp="#p_MTC1">Mann</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Brig. Gen. <persName>Howard McC. Snyder</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>General <persName>Patrick Hurley</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName>W. Alton Jones</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Colonel <persName>Robert Schulz</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Colonel <persName>Vernon Walters</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_OME1">Melville E. Osborne</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName>Robert Montgomery</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        <list>
                            <item>The President</item>
                            <item>The Foreign Minister</item>
                            <item>
                                <persName>Federico Mariscal</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Ambassador <persName>Carrillo Flores</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName>Humberto Romero</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName>Joaquin Bernal</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName>Justo Sierra</persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>Gen. <persName>José Gomez Huerta</persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>The President expressed his satisfaction with steps being taken to complete the
                    agreement between the United States and Mexico to permit rapid construction of
                    Amistad Dam. In recognition of the completion of Anzalduas Dam, the President
                    commented that it might be desirable to hold appropriate inauguration ceremonies
                    in the reasonably near future.</p>
                <p>The President made gifts to the Mexican President of a desk clock, an album of
                    photographs of the Mexican President’s visit to the United States in October
                    1959, and a silver-framed and autographed photograph of himself. He distributed
                    to the other members of the Mexican party specially made medallions
                    commemorating the occasion. The Mexican President presented silver-framed
                    photographs of himself to the President and to members of the President’s party.
                    He also presented to the President a silver model of the bell of Dolores
                    Hidalgo, the symbol of Mexico’s independence. The President noted its similarity
                    with the Liberty <persName corresp="#p_BJO1">Bell</persName> of Philadelphia and
                    the similarity of the traditions of liberty in the two countries.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d344fn2">In telegram 229 to Mexico City, October 22, the Department
                        transmitted the text of a joint communiqué issued following the meeting of
                        the two Presidents at Ciudad Acuña. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.,
                        711.11–EI/10–2060) For text of the joint communiqué, see Department of State
                            <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, December 5, 1960, p. 851.</note>
                </p>
